

*******************
Basic VM setup

1- Install latest distro of Kali Linux on VMWare 
2- Once installed, make sure the screen size is correct, go to your terminal and run:

cat /etc/apt/sources.list

If no repos are in there, add:
deb http://http.kali.org/kali kali-rolling main non-free contrib

This will allow you to update
$ sudo apt-get update

Then run the VMWare tools:

$apt-get install open-vm-tools-desktop fuse

Then reboot the machine, and adjust resolution on "Display" in settings
*******************
Once installed:
1- apt-get update
2- apt-get upgrade -y
3- apt-get dist-upgrade -y

